7 An Act relating to cities and towns; requiring
municipal bond proposals to contain one subject and
8 express subject in ballot title; clarifying that
multiple proposals shall be permitted; providing
9 circumstances that may determine whether proposal
violates act; allowing for the transfer of funds;
10 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 13-113 of Title 26, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Every municipal bond proposal to be voted on by the citizens
19 of that municipality shall contain only one subject and the subject
20 shall be expressed and defined in its ballot title.
21 B. Multiple bond proposals shall be permitted to be on the same
22 ballot, provided they require separate votes to be cast.
23 C. A bond proposal may violate this act if the monies raised
24 through the bond are appropriated and spent by more than a single
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3435 Page 1

1 agen cy, department, or director within the municipality unless
2 otherwise provided for in the ballot proposal. Nothing in this
3 section shall prevent funds from being transferred to another
4 department, director, or agency within the municipality, provided
5 that the funds are used for the project contained within the bond
6 proposal.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
8 Passed the House of Representatives the 11th day of March, 2026.
